data.description: This stunning 4-bedroom, 2.5-bath luxury rock home offers an unparalleled living experience. Nestled in a prime location, the front of the house boasts panoramic views of the Gatesville Gold Course, while the back overlooks the serene beauty of the Leon River.  The heart of the home is a chef's dream, featuring an enormous kitchen high lighted by a large rock bar area, custom cabinets, quartzite counters, upscale gas stove, a walk-in pantry, and a built-in China cabinet.  Kitchen opens to the den. The den itself is a cozy retreat, complete with a gas fireplace for those chilly evenings. The primary bedroom is a sanctuary with a huge window overlooking the picturesque back yard where deer often graze. It features a tray ceiling and primary bathroom with double walk-in closets, double sinks, a makeup area, and a luxurious whirlpool marble tub. Additional living spaces include an office with windows framing views of the Golf Course across the street, another living room, and a formal dining room. For practicality, the property includes a two-car attached garage and a detached garage/workshop. The large back patio is perfect for entertaining, and a rock trail leads to the river bottom with a delightful sitting area—an ideal spot for cookouts and camping. The property is conveniently close to schools, sitting right on the Golf Course, and offers direct access to nature through the back door. This home is a perfect blend of luxury, comfort, and natural beauty.  Seller will be remodeling the house soon and price will increase.
